# UX: a pasted "host:8443" carries its own port — parsed inline, the separate port step is
# SKIPPED (no KB[Port), and --set-server gets --port 8443.
desc wizard: host:port typed inline skips the port step
pick 0|Set up now
pick 0|https (secure, recommended)
kb 0|romm.example.com:8443
pick 0|Verify TLS certificate (recommended)
engine 0|RESULT server_set=1
kb 0|PAIR123
engine 0|RESULT paired=1 scopes_ok=1
kb 0|TrimUI Brick
engine 0|RESULT registered=1
engine 0|RESULT mirrored ok
pick 2|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --set-server https://romm.example.com --port 8443 -> rc=0
expect_trace_absent KB[Port
expect_config_has "root_uri": "https://romm.example.com"
expect_config_has "token"
